{
  "title": "Getting Started with React",
  "description": "Learn the fundamentals of React and build your first component. This comprehensive guide covers everything from JSX to hooks.",
  "slug": "getting-started-with-react",
  "author": "Sarah Johnson",
  "coverImage": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1633356122544-f134324a6cee?w=800",
  "layout": {
    "type": "single-column",
    "maxWidth": "1200px",
    "showTableOfContents": true
  },
  "settings": {
    "enableVoting": true,
    "enableSocialShare": true,
    "enableComments": true
  },
  "tags": ["React", "JavaScript", "Frontend", "Tutorial"],
  "links": [
    {
      "label": "Official React Docs",
      "url": "https://react.dev",
      "type": "external"
    },
    {
      "label": "React GitHub",
      "url": "https://github.com/facebook/react",
      "type": "external"
    }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "Introduction to React"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "React is a powerful JavaScript library for building user interfaces. Created by Facebook, it has become one of the most popular frontend frameworks in the world."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Why React?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "React makes it painless to create interactive UIs. Design simple views for each state in your application, and React will efficiently update and render just the right components when your data changes."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": {
        "variant": "info",
        "title": "Pro Tip",
        "content": "Start with Create React App for a quick setup without build configuration."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Installation"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": {
        "code": "npx create-react-app my-app\ncd my-app\nnpm start",
        "language": "bash"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Your First Component"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": {
        "code": "function Welcome(props) {\n  return <h1>Hello, {props.name}!</h1>;\n}",
        "language": "javascript",
        "filename": "Welcome.js"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "content": {
        "src": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1633356122544-f134324a6cee?w=800",
        "alt": "React logo and code",
        "caption": "React makes building UIs simple and efficient"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "content": {
        "text": "React makes it painless to create interactive UIs.",
        "author": "React Team"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "Congratulations! You've created your first React component. In the next sections, we'll explore more advanced concepts like hooks, state management, and performance optimization."
      }
    }
  ],
  "status": "published"
}

{
  "title": "TypeScript Best Practices for Modern Development",
  "description": "Discover essential TypeScript patterns and practices that will make your code more maintainable and type-safe.",
  "slug": "typescript-best-practices",
  "author": "Michael Chen",
  "coverImage": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516116216624-53e697fedbea?w=800",
  "layout": {
    "type": "two-column",
    "maxWidth": "1200px",
    "showTableOfContents": true
  },
  "settings": {
    "enableVoting": true,
    "enableSocialShare": true,
    "enableComments": true
  },
  "tags": ["TypeScript", "Programming", "Best Practices", "Development"],
  "links": [
    {
      "label": "TypeScript Handbook",
      "url": "https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/",
      "type": "external"
    }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "TypeScript Best Practices"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "TypeScript brings static type checking to JavaScript, helping you catch errors early and write more robust code. Here are some best practices to follow."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "1. Use Strict Mode"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "Always enable strict mode in your tsconfig.json. This enables a wide range of type checking behavior that results in stronger guarantees of program correctness."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": {
        "code": "{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true\n  }\n}",
        "language": "json",
        "filename": "tsconfig.json"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "2. Prefer Interfaces for Object Shapes"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": {
        "code": "interface User {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n}",
        "language": "typescript",
        "filename": "types.ts"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "3. Use Type Guards"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "Type guards help TypeScript narrow down types, making your code safer and more predictable."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": {
        "code": "function isString(value: unknown): value is string {\n  return typeof value === 'string';\n}",
        "language": "typescript",
        "filename": "guards.ts"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "content": {
        "text": "TypeScript is JavaScript with syntax for types.",
        "author": "TypeScript Documentation"
      }
    }
  ],
  "status": "published"
}

{
